TryHackMe: WhyHackMe – Full Walkthrough
Overview
WhyHackMe is a medium-difficulty room that combines web exploitation (XSS data exfiltration), privilege escalation via iptables, and decryption of TLS traffic to gain a reverse shell and finally root access.

Techniques used:

Anonymous FTP enumeration

Stored XSS to steal localhost-only credentials

SSH access as jack

Iptables rule modification to expose a hidden HTTPS backdoor

TLS decryption with server private key

Command injection via CGI script

Sudo misconfiguration (NOPASSWD: ALL) to become root

Flags:

